Commit Message: Propagated the ondisk option of kmetis to kway-initial partitioning
Optimized the symmetrization of dropedge-based coarsening.
Improved multi-way BFS and further refined LP-based refinement.
Propagating -niter in kmetis' rb-based initial partitioning
Exposed the -niparts option to the user.
Added per-vertex selection of mask-based contraction.
Updated the length of the mask-based hashing.
Switched the returned old2new mapping to partition-ordering based global numbering.
Remove an unnecessary path and simplify linking commands.
Updating to the latest GKlib version
fixed a memory bug that appears when the coarser graph stayed the same size as the original graph
Fixed a memory bug in coarsening
Small changes to reduce maximum memory use
Added extra max-memory used reporting sources
Fixed issue of k-way boundary of inconsistently ignoring island vertices.
Added some valgrind-compatible cmake options (off by default)

Fix various source comment and doc typos

Found via `codespell -q 3 -L ifset,ned,nd,`
Avoid out-of-bound memory access for empty graphs
Fixed incorrect part[] vector when nparts == 1
Cleaned up some old experimental modifications related to MIS-based initial partitioning experiments
issue #46: fixed the out-of-bound with mdeg+delta

Do not use unsupported -march flag on PPC
